cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.GT, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with transmission of information over a noisy channel and optimization of energy consumption. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper deals with scheduling of traffic over a communication channel. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with designing a scheduling policy to meet a hard deadline. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper uses dynamic programming to derive an optimal policy. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with transmission of packets of information.
